OL,6,FMs Badenoch accused Mr Staunton of
OL,7,Fmaking "wild baseless accusations" in
OL,8,Fa "blatant attempt to seek revenge"
OL,9,Fafter she sacked him last month, also
OL,10,Fclaiming he had been under
OL,11,Finvestigation for bullying at the time
OL,12,Fhe was fired.
OL,14,FMr Staunton then released his notes
OL,15,Ffrom his conversation with Ms Munby,
OL,16,Fwhere he says he was told to "rip off
OL,17,Fthe band aid" on its finances, but Ms
OL,18,FMunby said the funding discussed in
OL,19,Fthe memo was not to do with
OL,20,Fcompensation and denied all Mr
OL,21,FStaunton's claims.
